{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/blog/terminal-101---xargs/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>xargs is a command in Unix and Unix-like operating systems used to build and execute commands from standard input. It's particularly handy when you want to pass the output of one command as arguments to another command. Here are a few common use cases with examples:</p>\n<h2 id=\"deleting-multiple-files\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#deleting-multiple-files\" aria-label=\"deleting multiple files permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Deleting multiple files:</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sh\"><pre class=\"language-sh\"><code class=\"language-sh\"><span class=\"token function\">find</span> <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">.</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-name</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"*.txt\"</span> <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> <span class=\"token function\">xargs</span> <span class=\"token function\">rm</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>This command finds all files with a .txt extension in the current directory and its subdirectories, then passes them to xargs, which in turn executes rm (remove) command on each file.</p>\n<h2 id=\"creating-backups\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#creating-backups\" aria-label=\"creating backups permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Creating backups:</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sh\"><pre class=\"language-sh\"><code class=\"language-sh\"><span class=\"token function\">find</span> /path/to/files <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-type</span> f <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-print</span> <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> <span class=\"token function\">xargs</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-I</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token function\">cp</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> /path/to/backup</code></pre></div>\n<p>This command finds all files in /path/to/files, then uses xargs to copy each file to /path/to/backup.</p>\n<h2 id=\"running-commands-in-parallel\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#running-commands-in-parallel\" aria-label=\"running commands in parallel permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Running commands in parallel:</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sh\"><pre class=\"language-sh\"><code class=\"language-sh\"><span class=\"token function\">cat</span> list_of_urls.txt <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> <span class=\"token function\">xargs</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-P</span> <span class=\"token number\">5</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-n</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span> <span class=\"token function\">wget</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-q</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>This command reads a list of URLs from list_of_urls.txt, then uses xargs with -P option to run wget with up to 5 parallel processes, downloading each URL.</p>\n<h2 id=\"searching-for-files-containing-specific-text\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#searching-for-files-containing-specific-text\" aria-label=\"searching for files containing specific text permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Searching for files containing specific text:</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sh\"><pre class=\"language-sh\"><code class=\"language-sh\"><span class=\"token function\">grep</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-rl</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"search_term\"</span> /path/to/search <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> <span class=\"token function\">xargs</span> <span class=\"token function\">sed</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-i</span> <span class=\"token string\">'s/search_term/replace_term/g'</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>This command finds all files in /path/to/search containing \"search_term\", then uses xargs to pass each file to sed, replacing \"search_term\" with \"replace_term\".</p>","excerpt":"xargs is a command in Unix and Unix-like operating systems used to build and execute commands from standard input. It's particularly handyâ€¦","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#deleting-multiple-files\">Deleting multiple files:</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#creating-backups\">Creating backups:</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#running-commands-in-parallel\">Running commands in parallel:</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#searching-for-files-containing-specific-text\">Searching for files containing specific text:</a></li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"Terminal 101 - Xargs","date":"2024-05-15T00:00:00.000Z","slug":"/blog/terminal-101---xargs/","tags":["linux","terminal"],"cover_image":{"publicURL":"/static/5a3e4b781224e516688cc0507ed7b038/cover.png"}}}},"pageContext":{}},"staticQueryHashes":["3115057458"],"slicesMap":{}}